title: Bump serde from 1.0.95 to 1.0.97
body:
Bumps [serde](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde) from 1.0.95 to 1.0.97.
Release notes *Sourced from [serde's releases](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/releases).* > ## v1.0.97 > - Introduce `serde(try_from = "...")` attribute to derive Deserialize based on a given implementation of [`std::convert::TryFrom`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/convert/trait.TryFrom.html) ([#1526](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1526), thanks [@​fanzeyi](https://github.com/fanzeyi)) > > ```rust > #[derive(Deserialize)] > #[serde(try_from = "u32")] > enum N { > Zero, > One, > Two, > } > > impl TryFrom for N { > type Error = String; > > fn try_from(u: u32) -> Result { > match u { > 0 => Ok(Self::Zero), > 1 => Ok(Self::One), > 2 => Ok(Self::Two), > other => Err(format!("out of range: {}", other)), > } > } > } > ``` > > ## v1.0.96 > - Implement serialization and deserialization for std::sync::atomic types ([#1572](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1572) and [#1581](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1581), thanks [@​Roguelazer](https://github.com/Roguelazer)) > - Make "alloc" feature work on stable Rust 1.36+ ([#1576](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1576), thanks [@​c410-f3r](https://github.com/c410-f3r))
Commits - [`3ae2bee`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/3ae2bee272cd51ca65162646185043046751dc6d) Release 1.0.97 - [`d0fb958`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/d0fb958e99c2c00f7b6d6d1cffe7fabd3d74a64c) Remove unneeded explicit type parameters in test_from_into_traits - [`b941c63`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/b941c63a534b3360ce849010a6f2eef06d3299d9) More typical TryFrom usage for test - [`cf70c3f`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/cf70c3fb05d7ad7c3d7531c6150ac8c70bab8485) Format with rustfmt 2019-06-09 - [`f249e72`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/f249e72162fe59335f53f5e230bc511f4bbeb9a3) Provide try_from only on 1.34+ - [`92e0b62`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/92e0b62c6b39b34b7ef569666be8f6653b46e4e0) Merge pull request 1526 from fanzeyi/try_from - [`cf32a5b`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/cf32a5b20494eb40cd0efd15b1ea5ac412921321) Release 1.0.96 - [`7b0e06c`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/7b0e06c82569bdb72554e8ee61f1afab23a5a3e9) Provide 32 bit atomic impls for emscripten - [`3158bf9`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/3158bf9093fd8aff6bfbbd40e32ac7438bcf4e1d) Merge pull request [#1581](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1581) from Roguelazer/issue-1579 - [`01fade7`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/01fade764cdb902866fff666ed27f9869304453b) replaced one too many _ with - - Additional commits viewable in [compare view](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/compare/v1.0.95...v1.0.97)

title: Bump serde from 1.0.93 to 1.0.94

title: Bump serde_derive from 1.0.89 to 1.0.90
body:
Bumps [serde_derive](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde) from 1.0.89 to 1.0.90.
Release notes *Sourced from [serde_derive's releases](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/releases).* > ## v1.0.90 > - Add an attribute `#[serde(crate = "path::to::serde")]` which replaces the use of `extern crate serde` in the generated code; this is intended for crates that invoke Serde derives from a macro and need to refer to `serde` through their own re-export rather than requiring callers to list Serde in Cargo.toml ([#1499](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1499), thanks [@​sgrif](https://github.com/sgrif)) > > ```rust > #[derive(Deserialize)] > #[serde(crate = "__tw::codegen::serde")] > struct S { ... } > ``` > > ```rust > // expands to: > impl<'de> __tw::codegen::serde::Deserialize<'de> for S { > ... > } > ```
Commits - [`0be7f36`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/0be7f36d51164bb50b1f4dae452cc569030828e9) Release 1.0.90 - [`4c6cb6e`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/4c6cb6e359050e31b08fc16edfb106b810872c85) Match on serde_path to handle Some(path) and None - [`82bde8d`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/82bde8d1665e457a4e53cb7ef7ec9ec17d3cab0c) Format with rustfmt 2019-03-27 - [`465392b`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/465392b618310788ead7bb32f50a5d4a7ee4b04d) Merge pull request [#1499](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/serde-rs/serde/issues/1499) from sgrif/sg-custom-serde-path - [`f3c6b9f`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/f3c6b9f05a8df75f050680cc077368d723f8854c) Simplify signature of Container::serde_path - [`2f1945e`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/2f1945eaf27e8cf045430054c2f0c0542dd71fc0) Refer directly to serde_path in Deserialize impl - [`b4d8a55`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/b4d8a55b2ac2017598a9cccd5b4bceb4c180444e) Change `serde_path` to `crate` - [`0e6ce8f`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/0e6ce8fa508a556d4aa3f2f9e6b724fcaf842440) Fix for Rust 1.15 - [`a295c38`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/a295c38ba390d4db56dcb2195c3d3b24fb502901) Allow `#[serde(serde_path = "...")]` to override `extern crate serde` - [`295730b`](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/commit/295730ba1e8ccfb58afad836ea4907b951698aae) Clippy cyclomatic complexity lint has been renamed - Additional commits viewable in [compare view](https://github.com/serde-rs/serde/compare/v1.0.89...v1.0.90)

title: Bump env_logger from 0.6.0 to 0.6.1
body:
Bumps [env_logger](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger) from 0.6.0 to 0.6.1.
Release notes *Sourced from [env_logger's releases](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/releases).* > ## 0.6.1 > # Key Changes > > - Support better capturing for `cargo test` > - Don't print internal logs to `stdout` > > # Contributions > > - [@​nlopes](https://github.com/nlopes) [Fix path for rust-lang favicon](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/120) > - [@​emilio](https://github.com/emilio) [Don't print to stdout the warnings due to an invalid spec](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/126) > - [Support capturing for cargo test](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/127) > > # More Details > > ## `Builder::is_test` > > The `is_test` method can be used in tests to make sure logs are captured by `cargo test` the same way `println!` is: > > ```rust > fn init() { > let _ = env_logger::builder().is_test(true).try_init(); > } > > #[test] > fn it_adds_one() { > init(); > > info!("can log from the test too"); > assert_eq!(3, add_one(2)); > } > ``` > > There are performance implications of using `is_test` though, so it should be avoided outside of unit tests.

title: Bump openssl from 0.10.16 to 0.10.18
body:

title: Bump tempfile from 3.0.6 to 3.0.7
body:
Bumps [tempfile](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile) from 3.0.6 to 3.0.7.
Changelog *Sourced from [tempfile's changelog](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/blob/master/NEWS).* > 3.0.7 > ===== > > Breaking: > > * `Builder::prefix` and `Builder::suffix` now accept a generic `&AsRef`. > This could affect type inference. > * Temporary files (except unnamed temporary files on Windows and Linux >= 3.11) > now use absolute path names. This will break programs that create temporary > files relative to their current working directory when they don't have the > search permission (x) on some ancestor directory. This is only likely to > affect programs with strange chroot-less filesystem sandboxes. If you believe > you're affected by this issue, please comment on [#40](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/Stebalien/tempfile/issues/40). > > Features: > > * Accept anything implementing `&AsRef` in the builder: &OsStr, &OsString, &Path, etc. > > Fixes: > > * Fix LFS support. > * Use absolute paths for named temporary files to guard against changes in the > current directory. > * Use absolute paths when creating unnamed temporary files on platforms that > can't create unlinked or auto-deleted temporary files. This fixes a very > unlikely race where the current directory could change while the temporary > file is being created. > > Misc: > > * Use modern stdlib features to avoid custom unsafe code. This reduces the > number of unsafe blocks from 12 to 4.
Commits - [`251a76a`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/251a76a3c5e76cfcd90ea986764f6a5ab2d4e1be) release 3.0.7 - [`1df323e`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/1df323ebf90754e777d6dc8bdc674bf7c843a2de) Merge pull request [#83](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/Stebalien/tempfile/issues/83) from Stebalien/feat/even-safer - [`d1075d4`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/d1075d452afa6bc5819892a29ac4cb2cd617246c) use stdlib open options for creating unnamed temporary files - [`06fe67e`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/06fe67eb2e56e16baa0fb1c3c333abbf1b2a272a) Merge pull request [#82](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/Stebalien/tempfile/issues/82) from Stebalien/fix/modern-stdlib - [`8389b79`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/8389b79f2ed9216fa0f6734562f8ba3dbc8b875f) modernize stdlib usage - [`d7fac6b`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/d7fac6b6a02a3274c07f602a809b5ea74b955cc2) Merge pull request [#81](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/Stebalien/tempfile/issues/81) from Stebalien/fix/lfs-support - [`1065f44`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/1065f4412a7b6e686e4d06befa2dd9e9b6716d33) fix lfs support - [`3d5f762`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/3d5f762018629a4fa65ddbac51a23167167b7613) Merge pull request [#80](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/Stebalien/tempfile/issues/80) from Stebalien/fix/absolute-tempfile - [`951d1c6`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/951d1c6e15440357a9bc6fef6fe61b9553eaf8d3) make create_unlinked use absolute path names - [`d3ae2cf`](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/commit/d3ae2cf7297e3c8073ec6cc37a285de72fac7fec) make the path absolute when creating named temporary files - Additional commits viewable in [compare view](https://github.com/Stebalien/tempfile/compare/v3.0.6...v3.0.7)

title: delete unused dependencies
body:
delete .crate files and index files corresponding to the dependencies which are no longer used.
adding a command-line argument `--delete-unused` to opt-in this functionality


Note: I made the functionality as "opt-in" (`--delete-unused`) versus `cargo-vendor` which uses "opt-out" (`--no-delete`) so it's backwards compatible (but inconsistent with `cargo-vendor`). I would prefer breaking, but consistent change, but don't want this to be surprising to existing users. Let me know if you think it's okay to make a breaking change.

title: lowercase package name when building index
body:
When cargo looks for the package via index, it seems like it uses lowercased
package name. For example, "Inflector" package will be looked at "index/in/fl/inflector".

However, cargo-local-registry would create index entry at "index/In/fl/Inflector".
This would work fine on a case-insensitive filesystem (developer's Macbook laptop, for example),
but would fail on, for instance, Linux where file system is case-sensitive.

title: ignoring source overrides in local .cargo/config
body:
copying code from https://github.com/alexcrichton/cargo-vendor to
ignore source overrides in config

closes #79

title: Bump env_logger from 0.5.13 to 0.6.0
body:
Bumps [env_logger](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger) from 0.5.13 to 0.6.0.
Release notes *Sourced from [env_logger's releases](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/releases).* > ## 0.6.0 > # Key Changes > > - Set a policy for changes to the default format > - Make all dependencies besides `log` optional (but enabled by default) > > # Breaking Changes > > - The default format is not considered stable across patch versions. The best way to get a stable format for later ripgrepping is to define a custom one. > - All dependencies have been made optional except for `log`. That means compiling `env_logger` with `default-features=false` will result in a different experience than in `0.5.x`. > > # Contributions > > - [**hcpl**](https://github.com/hcpl) [Test with `-Z minimal-versions` on CI](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/114) > - [**afck**](https://github.com/afck) [Add missing RFC3339 URL to fix rustdoc](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/105) > - [Make all dependencies optional](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/100) > - [Rework the default format](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/82) > - [Don't clobber a previously set level filter](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/117) > > # More Details > > ## Disabling dependencies > > Using `default-features=false` will disable all dependencies of `env_logger` besides `log`. This will reduce compile times and alter the default format by disabling colours and timestamps. > > Disabling default dependencies is the recommended way to use `env_logger` for libraries that only need it for logging in tests.

Release notes *Sourced from [env_logger's releases](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/releases).* > ## 0.5.13 > # Key Changes > > - Add a public function for getting the default level style > > # Contributions > > - [**felixrabe**](https://github.com/felixrabe) [Typo](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/98) > - [**upsuper**](https://github.com/upsuper) [Move default level style to a public function](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/99) > - [**Eh2406**](https://github.com/Eh2406) [update some debs for minimal-versions](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/pull/101) > > # More Details > > ## `Formatter::default_level_style` > > The style used in the default format for printing level names can be fetched using the new `default_level_style` method on a `Formatter`. The below example will format just the record message using the style of its level: > > ```rust > builder.format(|buf, record| { > let level_style = buf.default_level_style(level); > write!(buf, "{} ", level_style.value(record.args())) > }); > ```
Commits - [`6b1b619`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/6b1b619986bf75b0f2bc88f4d0e281fada604c50) Merge pull request [#104](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/issues/104) from KodrAus/cargo/0.5.13 - [`c085ae8`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/c085ae8e1e72daad5dd12073011844a9ea5d4957) prepare for 0.5.13 release - [`27deaf1`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/27deaf163358607c58d8464f66539707d2aaf490) Merge pull request [#101](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/issues/101) from Eh2406/master - [`b139252`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/b13925217fa27c71d5fa93cbec56d81c958b2f29) update some debs for minimal-versions - [`66f7302`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/66f73025c9185569b7878bc56cca0e196cfe2ba3) Merge pull request [#99](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/issues/99) from upsuper/default_level_style - [`5014228`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/50142280718ed1d90feb4e053dbb01a4c9d0396f) Move default level style to a public function - [`561c9fb`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/561c9fb679dd7b091d50268b111d0d4010c8c28e) Merge pull request [#98](https://github-redirect.dependabot.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/issues/98) from felixrabe/patch-1 - [`4d1fa72`](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/commit/4d1fa722b145a6885839d85789da9c8a0599b75a) Typo - See full diff in [compare view](https://github.com/sebasmagri/env_logger/compare/v0.5.12...v0.5.13)

[![Dependabot compatibility score](https://api.dependabot.com/badges/compatibility_score?dependency-name=env_logger&package-manager=cargo&previous-version=0.5.12&new-version=0.5.13)](https://dependabot.com/compatibility-score.html?dependency-name=env_logger&package-manager=cargo&previous-version=0.5.12&new-version=0.5.13) Dependabot will resolve any conflicts with this PR as long as you don't alter it yourself.
